new.name: CMS-Made-Simple-2.2.9-Unauthenticated-SQL-Injection-Exploit-CVE-2019-9053-
new.description: This exploit targets an unauthenticated SQL injection vulnerability in CMS Made Simple <= 2.2.9 (CVE-2019-9053). It uses a time-based blind SQL injection to extract the username, email, and password hash from the database. Additionally, it supports password cracking using a wordlist.
